The recommended dosage of Feridex I.V. (ferumoxides injectable solution)  is 0.56 milligrams of iron (0.05 mL Feridex I.V. (ferumoxides injectable solution) ) per kilogram of body weight, that is diluted in 100 mL of 5% dextrose solution and given over 30 minutes. (See Drug Preparation Section). The diluted drug is administered through a 5 micron filter at a rate of 2 to 4 milliliters per minute.
Feridex I.V. (ferumoxides injectable solution)  should not be administered undiluted.
Post-contrast imaging may begin immediately after the dose is infused and may be performed up to 3.5 hours after the end of the infusion. T2-weighted pulse sequences provide the maximum contrast effect.
